# QA Automation Rules

## Always do

- Read `.env` for `BASE_URL` and app config before starting
- Read `code-context/` before generating any tests
- Use `helpers/navigation.ts` `gotoWithRetry()` for all navigation
- Use `page-objects/` locators — never hardcode selectors
- Use `constants/routes.ts` — never hardcode URLs
- Run `npx tsc --noEmit` after every code change and fix all errors

## Never do

- Invent selectors not confirmed in `page-maps/`
- Hardcode URLs — use ROUTES constants
- Recreate helpers that already exist in `helpers/`
- Commit `auth/`, `page-maps/`, `code-context/`, or `.env`
- Use `.then()` promise chains — always use `async/await`

## File structure

```
tests/baseline/    → page load and element visibility tests
tests/e2e/         → full user flow tests
tests/regression/  → edge cases and negative tests
tests/marketing/   → public / landing page tests
page-objects/      → one class per page, grouped by role
helpers/           → shared utilities
constants/         → routes and other constants
fixtures/          → Playwright test fixtures
```

## When generating tests

- Read `prompts/03-generate-baseline.md` for baseline tests
- Read `prompts/04-generate-e2e.md` for e2e tests
- Read `prompts/05-generate-regression.md` for regression tests
- Follow the existing patterns in `page-objects/` exactly

## Prompt files reference

All task prompts are in `prompts/`. Read the relevant one before starting any task.
